CatDescriptText: Mrs. Joseph Tames, 2610 Mahon Street and Donald Jefferson, 2490 Centre Avenue, were part of the "Pittsburghers Speak Up" column published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, July 12, 1958, pg. 2 with question: "Should well-defined courses in sex education be taught in public school system? If so, at what grade should the teaching of these courses begin?" answer reads: "I believe they should receive a well-defined course around the age of 14."
